  <sect2>
    <title>Installation</title>

    <para>
      Prepare the package for compilation:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>./configure --prefix= \
            --disable-nls \
            --with-xkb-rules-symlink=xorg</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Compile the package:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Install the package:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>porg -lD "make pkgconfigdir=/lib/pkgconfig -j1 install"</userinput></screen>

    <sect3>
      <title>Command Explanations</title>

      <para>
        <parameter>--with-xkb-rules-symlink=xorg</parameter>: By default, the
        XKB rules installed are named "base". This creates symlinks named "xorg"
        to those rules, which is the default name used by Xorg.
      </para>

    </sect3>

  </sect2>

